In article <27tr36$qda@news.delphi.com> anspring@news.delphi.com (ANSPRING@DELPHI.COM) writes:
>
>Differential cryptanalyis is a cryptanalytic technique introduced into the 
>open literature by Eli Biham and Adi Shamir in 1990.  It is designed to
>produce information about a cipher by examining the differences in
>ciphertext caused by differences in plaintext.  For example, in the 
>Crypto '91 proceedings, B&S show that the key to a 16-Round DES-like 

I've seen mention of it here a few months ago, but there is a wonderfully
detailed book on this which was recently issued by Springer-Verlag.

Differential Cryptanalysis of the Data Encryption Standard
Biham, E. and Shamir, A.
ISBN 0-387-97930-1,3-540-97930-1
1993

Price in the U.S. is just under $40

